cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.ST, cs.NE 

This paper deals with machine learning algorithms for regression tasks, specifically adaptive nonlinear regression using tree-based piecewise linear regression. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as these sub-categories are closely related to machine learning. The paper also involves statistical analysis and modeling, which makes cs.ST (Statistics) a likely sub-category. Finally, the use of regressor and partitioning functions suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be a relevant sub-category.
